## Firebase Data Model (Firestore Collections)

```
/properties/{propertyId}
  - name: string
  - slug: string
  - description: string
  - shortDescription: string
  - heroImage: string (Storage URL)
  - photos: array of { url: string, order: number, caption?: string }
  - amenities: array of { name: string, category: string, icon: string }
  - location: { address: string, lat: number, lng: number, nearbyAttractions: array }
  - houseRules: array of string
  - specs: { bedrooms: number, bathrooms: number, maxGuests: number, sqft: number }
  - pricing: {
      baseRate: number,
      cleaningFee: number,
      taxRate: number,
      minNights: number,
      seasonalRates: array of { name: string, startDate: timestamp, endDate: timestamp, rate: number }
    }
  - cancellationPolicy: string
  - active: boolean
  - createdAt: timestamp
  - updatedAt: timestamp

/bookings/{bookingId}
  - propertyId: string (ref to property)
  - guestName: string
  - guestEmail: string
  - guestPhone: string
  - checkIn: timestamp
  - checkOut: timestamp
  - numGuests: number
  - nightlyRate: number (rate at time of booking)
  - numNights: number
  - cleaningFee: number
  - taxes: number
  - totalPrice: number
  - status: "confirmed" | "pending" | "cancelled" | "completed"
  - stripeSessionId?: string
  - stripePaymentIntentId?: string
  - specialRequests?: string
  - ownerNotes?: string
  - isManualBlock: boolean (true if owner-created block)
  - createdAt: timestamp
  - updatedAt: timestamp

/reviews/{reviewId}
  - propertyId: string
  - bookingId?: string
  - guestName: string
  - rating: number (1-5)
  - text: string
  - ownerResponse?: string
  - approved: boolean
  - source: "direct" | "manual" (manual = imported from other platform)
  - createdAt: timestamp

/siteSettings/{settingsId}
  - brandName: string
  - tagline: string
  - contactEmail: string
  - contactPhone: string
  - aboutText: string
  - socialLinks: { instagram?: string, facebook?: string }
  - updatedAt: timestamp
```

---

## API Routes (Next.js `/app/api/`)

- `POST /api/create-checkout-session` — Creates a Stripe Checkout session with booking details. Stores a pending booking in Firestore.
- `POST /api/webhooks/stripe` — Stripe webhook listener. On `checkout.session.completed`, update booking status to "confirmed" and send confirmation email.
- `POST /api/send-email` — Sends booking confirmation or contact form emails via Resend/SendGrid.
- `GET /api/availability/[propertySlug]` — Returns blocked date ranges for a property (from confirmed bookings and manual blocks). Used by the front-end calendar.
- `POST /api/bookings/cancel` — Admin-initiated cancellation. Updates Firestore, processes Stripe refund if applicable.

---

## Key Implementation Details

### Availability Calendar Logic
- Query Firestore for all bookings where `propertyId` matches and `status` is "confirmed" or `isManualBlock` is true.
- Build an array of blocked date ranges.
- On the front-end calendar component, disable these dates.
- When a user selects dates, validate server-side that the dates are still available before creating the Stripe session (prevent double-booking race conditions).

### Pricing Calculation
- For selected date range, check each night against seasonal rate overrides.
- If a night falls within a seasonal range, use that rate; otherwise use the base rate.
- Sum nightly rates + cleaning fee + (subtotal × tax rate) = total.
- Show this breakdown clearly in the booking widget and checkout page.

### Image Handling
- Upload to Firebase Storage under `/properties/{propertyId}/photos/`.
- Store download URLs in Firestore property document.
- Use Next.js `<Image>` component with Firebase Storage URLs. Configure `next.config.js` to allow Firebase Storage domain in `images.remotePatterns`.
- In admin photo manager, use drag-and-drop (react-beautiful-dnd or dnd-kit) for reordering.

### Auth & Route Protection
- Use Firebase Auth with email/password for the owner.
- Create a React context (`AuthProvider`) that wraps the app and exposes the current user.
- All `/admin/*` routes check for authenticated user. If not authenticated, redirect to `/admin/login`.
- Use Next.js middleware (`middleware.ts`) to protect admin routes server-side as well.

### SEO & Performance
- Use Next.js metadata API for page titles, descriptions, Open Graph tags.
- Add structured data (JSON-LD) for `LodgingBusiness` and `VacationRental` schema types.
- Lazy-load images below the fold.
- Use `next/font` for Google Fonts loading optimization.
- Generate a `sitemap.xml` and `robots.txt`.

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach.
- Booking widget: sticky sidebar on desktop (lg+), sticky bottom bar on mobile.
- Photo gallery: full-width stacked on mobile, grid on desktop.
- Admin dashboard: sidebar collapses to top hamburger on mobile.
- Test all flows at 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px.

